ğŸš€ Quick Start
Prerequisites
Python 3.8 or higher

Google Gemini API key

Installation
Clone the repository

bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd zero-hunger-chef
Create virtual environment

bash
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
Install dependencies

bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
Environment setup
Create a .env file:

env
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key-here
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key-here
Initialize database

bash
flask --app app.py _init_db
Run the application

bash
python app.py
Visit the application
Open http://127.0.0.1:5000 in your browser

ğŸ¯ How to Use
1. Get Started
Visit the homepage and create an account

No payment required - completely free!

2. Generate Recipes
Go to the Dashboard

Enter ingredients you have available (comma-separated)

Click "Generate Recipe" to get AI-powered suggestions

3. Manage Your Recipes
View your complete recipe history

Search and filter recipes

Copy recipes to clipboard

Regenerate new variations

4. Example Usage
text
Input: "chicken, rice, broccoli, garlic"
Output: A complete recipe with instructions for a balanced meal
ğŸ”§ Configuration
Environment Variables
SECRET_KEY: Flask secret key for session security

GOOGLE_API_KEY: Your Google Gemini API key

Database
The application uses SQLite by default with models for:

Users: Authentication and user management

RecipeHistory: Stores all generated recipes with timestamps

AI Configuration
Primary model: gemini-2.0-flash-001

Fallback models for reliability

Creative temperature settings for varied recipes

ğŸŒŸ Key Features in Detail
Smart Recipe Generation
Context-Aware: Understands ingredient combinations

Nutrition-Focused: Emphasizes balanced, healthy meals

Waste-Reducing: Maximizes use of available ingredients

Practical: Realistic cooking times and instructions

Beautiful User Interface
Modern Design: Clean, professional appearance

Responsive: Works perfectly on mobile and desktop

Interactive: Smooth animations and transitions

Accessible: Clear navigation and user feedback

Recipe Management
Complete History: Never lose a recipe

Smart Search: Find recipes by ingredients or content

Easy Sharing: Copy recipes with one click

Quick Regeneration: Create new versions instantly

ğŸ”’ Security Features
Secure Authentication: Flask-Login with password hashing

Session Management: Secure user sessions

Input Validation: Sanitized user inputs

SQL Injection Protection: SQLAlchemy ORM

ğŸ“± Responsive Design
The application is fully responsive and optimized for:

Desktop (1200px+): Full feature set with multi-column layouts

Tablet (768px-1199px): Adapted layouts with maintained functionality

Mobile (<768px): Streamlined single-column design with touch-friendly interfaces

ğŸ› ï¸ Development
Running in Development Mode
bash
python app.py
# or
flask --app app.py run --debug
Database Management
bash
# Initialize database
flask --app app.py _init_db

# Debug database (DEV)
http://127.0.0.1:5000/_debug_db
API Testing
bash
# Test history API (while logged in)
http://127.0.0.1:5000/api/history

# Debug models
http://127.0.0.1:5000/_debug_models
ğŸš€ Deployment
For Production
Set DEBUG=False in environment

Use production WSGI server (Gunicorn)

Configure proper database (PostgreSQL recommended)

Set up reverse proxy (Nginx)

Configure SSL certificates

Environment Setup
env
SECRET_KEY=your-production-secret-key
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-gemini-api-key
DATABASE_URL=your-database-connection-string
